15 §2354.11. Premortem interventions; definitions; prohibitions
16 A. For purposes of this Section, "premortem intervention" means any
17 medical procedure, test, medication, cannulation, or other intervention
18 undertaken prior to the determination of death for the purpose of facilitating
19 organ or tissue recovery.
20 B. No premortem intervention shall be performed unless it is medically
21 indicated for the direct benefit of the patient or is performed pursuant to a
22 legally effective consent applicable to premortem interventions, as provided in
23 this Section.
24 C. Regardless of consent, no person shall perform or direct any
25 premortem intervention that has a material likelihood of any of the following:
26 (1) Hastening death.
27 (2) Manufacturing, accelerating, or securing irreversibility of
28 circulatory, respiratory, or neurologic cessation.
29 (3) Preventing or materially interfering with the restoration or
30 resumption of circulatory, respiratory, or neurologic function.
