14 §2354.14. Out-of-state anatomical gift decisions; effect
15 A. An anatomical gift decision, including an authorization or refusal,
16 made in another state that is valid under the laws of that state or of this state
17 shall be recognized as a legally effective anatomical gift decision in this state.
18 B. The effect of an anatomical gift decision recognized under this Section
19 shall be determined in accordance with the laws of this state.
20 C. If multiple anatomical gift decisions exist, including decisions made
21 in another state, the most recent legally effective authorization or refusal shall
22 control.
23 D. If the laws of another state conflict with the provisions of this Part, the
24 provisions of this Part shall govern the determination of the effect of the
25 anatomical gift decision.
26 E. Notwithstanding any provision of another state's law, an anatomical
27 gift decision made by a minor shall not constitute a legally effective
28 authorization or refusal in this state.
